          "message": {
            "text": "An issue was discovered in Django 2.0 before 2.0.3, 1.11 before 1.11.11, and 1.8 before 1.8.19. If django.utils.text.Truncator's chars() and words() methods were passed the html=True argument, they were extremely slow to evaluate certain inputs due to a catastrophic backtracking vulnerability in a regular expression. The chars() and words() methods are used to implement the truncatechars_html and truncatewords_html template filters, which were thus vulnerable. The older branches are unsupported and might be vulnerable as well."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "logicalLocations": [
                {
                  "name": "read",
                  "properties": {
                    "FullName": "StreamingBuffer||.read",
