        },
        {
          "message": {
            "text": "An issue was discovered in Django prior to 4.2.16, 5.0.x prior to 5.0.9, and 5.1.x prior to 5.1.1. The 'django.contrib.auth.forms.PasswordResetForm' class, when used in a view implementing password reset flows, allows remote attackers to enumerate user e-mail addresses by sending password reset requests and observing the outcome (only when e-mail sending is consistently failing)."
          },
          "locations": [
